cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SI, cs.DS 

The paper presents a neural network technique for the analysis and extrapolation of time-series data, which falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of neural networks and activation functions suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The focus on time-series data and decomposition of sinusoids suggests that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the comparison with popular time-series forecasting techniques suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as well.
